This paper is about automated visual inspection in the semiconductor industry using deep neural networks. The paper focuses on the development of a novel deep neural network-based hybrid approach for detecting and classifying manufacturing defects in high-resolution imagery. The approach involves stacked hybrid convolutional neural networks (SH-CNN) and draws inspiration from current approaches of visual attention. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-category for this paper is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). 

The paper also involves machine learning approaches, which require a tremendous amount of computational effort. Therefore, it is also likely to belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning). 

The paper introduces a novel deep neural network-based hybrid approach, which involves the use of convolutional neural networks (CNNs). Therefore, it is also likely to belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). 

The paper also involves the use of neural networks, which are a type of computational model inspired by the structure and function of the human brain. Therefore, it is also likely to belong to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). 

Finally, the paper involves the use of high-resolution imagery, which is a type of multimedia data. Therefore, it is also likely to belong to cs.MM (Multimedia).
